            <a:r>
              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>Here's the thing about reliability: we never crash or return empty. We have a cascade of recovery strategies. Strategy 1: the LLM produced a complete answer, return it. Strategy 2: if finish_reason was 'length', the LLM was cut off — we still return the partial output with a truncation notice. Strategy 3 (RAG Tool Fallback): if a rag_agent_tool returned valid JSON with 'answer' and 'citations' keys, we extract that directly. Strategy 4 (Tool Result Synthesis): we collect ALL tool call outputs from the message history and make a SECOND LLM call with a synthesis prompt. Strategy 5 is absolute last resort: a user-friendly error message. Each path is logged with reason codes for observability.</a:t>
            </a:r>
          </a:p>
        </p:txBody>
